<!-- BEGIN-FUNC new -->
NAME
  vcam::new - run vcam in background mode

SYNOPSIS
  vcam::new( files <, options> <, attr>)
  vcam( files <, options> <, attr=value> )

PARAMETER
  files   - list of equations "inputfile"=outputfile"  or a
            list of lists ["inputfile"=outputfile",[t,...]]
            where 't' is a timestamp between TimeBegin and
            TimeEnd of an animation.
  options - either Check, Remove or Verbose
  attr    - further attributes

DESCRIPTION
  For each input file, the function starts a vcam process to create
  one output file or a sequence of output files (if a list of time-
  stamps is specified), respectively.

  The format of the output file is specified by the suffix of the
  corresponding file name, e.g., png, jpg, gif, avi,...

  If a list of timestamps is given, any token '%n' within an output
  file name is substituted by the index of the current timestamp in
  the list of timestamps.

  Timestamps must be numerical values between TimeBegin and TimeEnd
  of an animation.

  The function returns the list of created output files in the order
  they were created.
  
  Available options of the module function:

  Remove  - remove the input file after the corresponding output file
            has been created.
  Verbose - print a progress report to the screen.

  Vcam attributes:

  ReduceColors     -  Reduce to 256 colors, may be useful for some
                      raster image formats in order to reduce the
                      images size. The default is not to reduce
                      colors.
  Resolution = nn  -  Resolution of resulting raster image, given
                      in dots per inch (DPI). The default value is
                      the resolution of the computers display.
  Quality = nn     -  Quality value for JPEG output, 3D EPS shading
                      or AVI output. A percentage value. The default
                      is 75%.
  Frames = nn      -  Number of frames per second for AVI output.
                      The default is 15.
  Mode = nn        -  Output mode, depends on the output format. May
                      be used for JPEG, 3D EPS and AVI output:

                      JPEG Output
                      0    baseline sequential (the default mode)
                      1    progressive (may not be supported by
                           every display software)
                      2    sequential optimized
                      3D EPS Output
                      0    painters algorithm (the default mode)
                      1    BSP tree algorithm
                      AVI Output
                      0    Microsoft Video 1 codec (the default mode)
                      1    uncompressed single frame codec
                      2    Radius Cinepak codec

EXAMPLES
  >> plot(plot::Function2d(sin(x)),OutputFile=NOTEBOOKPATH."Sin.xvc")

  >> vcam( [NOTEBOOKPATH."Sin.xvc"=NOTEBOOKPATH."Sin.png"],
           Verbose, Remove, Resolution=300)

     File[1/1]:
     in : C:\Dokumente und Einstellungen\andi\Eigene Dateien\Sin.xvc
     out: C:\Dokumente und Einstellungen\andi\Eigene Dateien\Sin.png

  >> plot(plot::Function2d(sin(k*x), x=-5..5,k=-1..1),OutputFile=NOTEBOOKPATH."MUFF\\ani.xvc")

  >> vcam(Verbose, [[NOTEBOOKPATH."MUFF\\ani.xvc"=NOTEBOOKPATH."MUFF\\muff-%n.png",
                     [0.5*k $ k=0..20]
                   ]]):

     File[1/1]:
     in : C:\Dokumente und Einstellungen\andi\Eigene Dateien\ani.xvc
     out: C:\Dokumente und Einstellungen\andi\Eigene Dateien\muff-001.png
     time: 0.000000
     ...

